http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Confined-woman-baby-%E2%80%98rescued%E2%80%99-by-village-residents/article14009962.ece

A 35-year-old woman, who was allegedly being confined and tortured by her mother-in-law at her residence, was rescued by the residents of Swarnasandra here on Tuesday evening.On receiving the information, the Mandya East police visited the spot and shifted the victim, Chethana Kumari, and her six-month-old baby boy to the Mandya Institute of Medical Sciences (MIMS) hospital for treatment. Ms. Kumari of H. Malligere in Mandya taluk had been staying with husband Umesha, a cab driver, in Bengaluru. However, she recently returned to her mother-in-law, Ratnamma’s residence, with her son, when the harassment began.Mandya City Municipal Council (CMC) member Pushpalatha and others rescued them, a senior police officer said. According to her neighbour, the victim was exhausted when they went to her house. However, Superintendent of Police T.J. Udesha (Mandya subdivision) said it was just a domestic fight. “We will register the FIR, if Ms. Kumari files a complaint,” he said.